app.comment: A drawing library that mimics Khan Academy tutorials.

PtRadBbkSeU9S4Dis6XmV440.text: The actions in this library mimics the environment from Khan Academy CS at https://www.khanacademy.org/cs/.

xRlIXydzNJLlQ14G1dfO0I5p.text: This library provides an easy way to create a canvas and perform basic drawing operations on it. A lot of the actions are similar to the functions found in the Khan Academy excersises.

cm4VI3DfaQJHf8MyrGixmfYn.text: Displays the canvas on the screen

jVrEfY9jHA04fu14t6DPssHR.text: Displays a new full screen canvas in a [](/box)

aRZEXF3gkY2NalyC0PoYPKN2.text: Creates a new canvas. Use ``post to wall`` to display it on the screen

oxRWwXkwU44De5CV4S6DDbqx.text: You can use this library with [boxes](/box) and observe the result of your changes as you type in the live view.

qsyFW5b4glz6GA4tpS4tOZ7y.text: * use `code->show canvas` to create a new canvas in a box

IoTGkbxW4yD01MKkkULATbqs.text: Takes the cosine of an angle in degrees.

xLW3OsG71Lll4DWKoiFXERe8.text: Takes the cosine of an angle in degrees.
Takes the sine of an angle in degrees.

JVWXaND4r6xxGcCw8UzIUcQJ.text: Takes the sine of an angle in degrees.
Takes the tangent of an angle in degrees.

x8yb5ADnJwEdQVhdjP7rDlcM.text: Raises a number to an exponent.

x1qHTcgh72QqQwiXEpyaQ54v.text: Changes the size of the text

QXb5nh4W4fdTVZfcjtPpOjis.text: Gets the width of the canvas in pixels

WUm58F4bsRWPZ1hnVvmKWM1N.text: Gets the width of the canvas in pixels
Gets the height of the canvas in pixels

jxDtruNGareofMmEMG4P46lc.text: Saves the canvas image to the picture library

kRyC1SShuZofdJ5yyH8O8tNL.text: * add a new line in the `[display]` section

ZiiNHBlT8EiatE6Nm9nYB0Jv.text: Before we can start drawing, we need to post a canvas on the screen. The canvas is where all the drawing happens.

buNZWvuX9OrR94PL63iTStO5.text: You can draw rectangles, circles and lines.

J6Wl7aCCIxqD542144Mz0l46.text: Draws a rectangle. `x` and `y` are the upper left coordinates.

FkNCRcHuDi8ndS4Vu3Cd9nKO.text: You can change the **fill** and **stroke** color.

z2f8l2bpLLh6g3XTAvvD2PQm.text: * changing the fill color used to paint shapes

QCPirl9zPA68kB4SD4TFacBS.text: * changing the stroke color used to color outlines

xNDr56n9Fcs1ugZQPBfkF04T.text: * changing the thickness of the outline

xQWN0nJybWbkysUmAg0dVNQc.text: Draws horizontal and vertical axis and a grid

u5thU8VUR0AWhFWvFnkdOgfC.text: The canvas uses the screen coordinate system. The origin is on the top left corner; the horizontal axis goes left to right and the vertical axis goes top to bottom.

The canvas uses the screen coordinate system. The origin is on the top left corner; the horizontal axis goes left to right and the vertical axis goes top to bottom. You can draw a grid that makes it easier to understand by using ``grid``.
